edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.logic.Comparison.Operator

public abstract static class Comparison.Operator extends Object implements Comparable<Comparison.Operator>, Serializable, Unique
An operator is a singleton object that represents one of the possible binary relationship between the left and right expressions of a comparison.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • simplify

      public Expression simplify(Expression left, Expression right)
      If a comparison using this operator with the given left and right expressions can be simplified, this method returns the simplified expression; otherwise it returns null. The most common case in which a comparison can be simplified is when its left and right expressions are both values, in which case this method returns true if this operator's test method returns true, and false if this operator's test method returns false.
      Parameters:
      left - the left expression of a comparison
      right - the right expression of a comparison
      Returns:
      a simplified expression or null if the comparison cannot be simplified
